{"answer_uniqueness_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"artifact_id":"q-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","artifact_type":"question","author":{"identity":"openai-codex-sap-org-04-content-author","identity_type":"model","role":"lesson_question_author"},"blueprint_references":[{"blueprint_id":"aws-sap-c02-assessment-blueprint","canonical_digest":"3362d465a410c84d40250cd3b6dcfa5ac80cfc25d0b8d7b034b45327b8049d8d","version":"0.3A.1"}],"canonical_digest":"ce49e0de8b8b943ec994354759d4a5662c9a7cf5326f8e6d36bf7a111dac3bc6","content_review_state":{"approval":null,"status":"pending"},"created_at":"2026-07-19T21:30:00Z","keyed_option_ids":["a"],"learner_explanation":"Option A is best. For a supported type with organization sharing enabled, RAM can target accounts in an OU while the platform account retains ownership. The RAM permission is a ceiling, and consumer identities still need applicable allows. Duplicating the resource violates the ownership and overhead requirements. A broad administrator role does not implement the scoped resource-share model. A shared Regional resource is consumed in the Region where it exists in the owner account.","modified_at":"2026-07-19T21:29:00Z","objective_references":{"primary":"SAP-ORG-04","supporting":["SAP-FND-01","SAP-FND-02","SAP-ORG-02"]},"option_rationales":[{"category":"key_support","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1}],"is_keyed":true,"option_id":"a","rationale":"It satisfies ownership, OU targeting, layered permission, Region, and overhead requirements.","requirement_ids":["req-owner","req-scope","req-access","req-overhead"]},{"category":"excessive_operational_burden","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"b","rationale":"Copies transfer ownership to each account and recreate the administration the scenario asks to avoid.","requirement_ids":["req-owner","req-overhead"]},{"category":"wrong_security_boundary","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"c","rationale":"A broad administrator role is not the scoped RAM share and permission model required by the scenario.","requirement_ids":["req-scope","req-access"]},{"category":"unstated_assumption","claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1}],"is_keyed":false,"option_id":"d","rationale":"The option assumes global access that the approved Regional-resource behavior does not provide.","requirement_ids":["req-access"]}],"options":[{"option_id":"a","text":"Create an AWS RAM resource share for the supported resource, target the selected OU, choose the appropriate RAM permission, and grant consumer identities only the required operations."},{"option_id":"b","text":"Copy the resource into every application account and let each team own and administer its copy."},{"option_id":"c","text":"Grant a broad cross-account administrator role into the platform account instead of creating a resource share."},{"option_id":"d","text":"Create a RAM share in one Region and require consumers to access the Regional resource from any Region as though it were global."}],"originality_review_state":{"review":null,"status":"pending"},"question_id":"q-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","question_type":"single_response","required_selection_count":1,"requirement_option_matrix":[{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-owner"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-scope"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"d","result":"fails"}],"requirement_id":"req-access"},{"cells":[{"option_id":"a","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"b","result":"fails"},{"option_id":"c","result":"satisfies"},{"option_id":"d","result":"satisfies"}],"requirement_id":"req-overhead"}],"revision":1,"schema_version":"ala.authoring.question.v1","source_citation_projection":[{"canonical_digest":"40ade314f1a81ccd854f670963fa5b08f5ea88b6424348895b45f2206547e694","locator":"See the cited official AWS section named in the approved source record.","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-ram-overview"},{"canonical_digest":"cb36a0e0a212531d835e7f2462f72370e097b3641c7f23ae4555fe8ce275e2a9","locator":"See the cited official AWS section named in the approved source record.","revision":1,"source_id":"src-b-ram-sharing"}],"specification_reference":{"artifact_id":"qspec-sap-org-04-resource-sharing","artifact_type":"question_spec","canonical_digest":"f54a02eaae66e7af7fa8f47c96b794873708e5bc9c747ff5c318c394c3208944","revision":1},"status":"draft","stem":"A platform account owns a Regional resource type that the current AWS RAM documentation lists as supported. Application accounts in one OU must use the resource in the Region where it exists. The platform team must retain ownership, consumer actions must remain limited by both the share and consumer identity permissions, and the company wants to avoid one copy per account. Organization sharing is enabled through AWS RAM. Which design best meets these requirements?","supersedes":null,"supporting_claim_references":[{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-owner","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"6e4d2c4137533df10b7fe5f92ac266344fbbb4a9918781bd74b8b9454d7432b4","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-permission-ceiling","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"a2b93808d2a2d0c8085a6a3f5f562e2c12751732471ae32d3400164231c94c5e","revision":1},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-principals","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1932fbdba3837d6ae8f9e8e3660adc78c7af0e2dd78ce5d1973212b5dbc77980","revision":3},{"artifact_id":"clm-b-ram-regional","artifact_type":"claim","canonical_digest":"1ab0e879de5d9feb8aae5fca0afe866a1a5d1db4f838da47ef88fd7fe10edf12","revision":1}],"validation_state":{"report":null,"status":"not_run"}}
